examples.en: They try to keep up appearances.
I am a great observer of natural appearances.
You make a mistake if you go by appearances.
Don't be misled by appearances, he's a good worker.
He appears to be happy, but appearances can be deceptive.
He was, to all appearances, a respectable, successful businessman.
She likes to make dramatic appearances wearing her trademark outsize sunglasses.
The candidates' public appearances were carefully staged (=not natural).
Remember that appearances can deceive  just because something looks good doesn't mean it is good.
To all outward appearances everything was fine, but under the surface the marriage was very shaky.
